      <small>sIFR Documentation and FAQ</small><br />
      Firefox Greasemonkey Scripts
    
  </h1>

  

<p>There are two user scripts available for <a href="http://greasemonkey.mozdev.org/">Greasemonkey</a> which allow you to remove the sIFR elements from a page. This can be useful if, for example, you are using FlashBlock, which blocks these elements.</p>

<p>The first script provides some tools such as removing the sIFR elements and a way to execute the replacement statements if you're debugging. It requires GreaseMonkey 0.2.6. <a href="http://novemberborn.net/sifr/greasemonkey/sifr-tools.user.js">sIFR Tools</a>.</p>

<p>The second script disables sIFR. <a href="http://novemberborn.net/sifr/greasemonkey/sifr-disable.user.js">Install here</a></p>

